column1: Data Contact: Dr. Eduardo S. Brondizio (ebrondiz@indiana.edu) or Dr. Emilio F. Moran (moran@indiana.edu)

column4: X coordinates of center of site or site border - UTM, Brazil sites are generally Zone 22S, WGS84, Yapu site is Zone 19S,
Y coordinates of center of site or site border - UTM, Brazil sites are generally Zone 22S, WGS84, Yapu site is Zone 19S

Sampling location name (Altamira, Bragantina, Ponta de Pedras, Tome-Acu, Yapu) (sites of Acai (Euterpe oleracea) agroforestry are not included for the Ponta de Pedras region; agroforestry sites not included for Tome-Acu)
Sample ID: site code + year of inventory, (e.g. A001-92, B001-92, P001-92, T001-02, YA008-95) (soil sampling was also carried out at each site, from 0 to 1 meter at 20 cm intervals)
Land use type reported (years of use)
Land use/land cover history with dates where available
Number of individual plants (understory) per hectare
Number of individual plants (overstory) per hectare

column2: Missing data values are represented as -9999.

column9: 1950s-forest (old growth); 1950s-60s -repeated slash-and-burning until 1966; 1966-fallow (repeated burning almost every year)
